 East London - Police in East London have opened an inquest docket following the drowning of two learners from a primary school in Mthatha while they were swimming at Eastern beach, East London, at about 12:15 on Friday. "According to information, it is said that the learners were swimming in the sea when they experienced difficulty," said police spokesperson, Captain Mluleki Mbi. "Two learners, a boy and a girl of 13 and 14 years of age, were declared dead on the scene by paramedics. "Their identities will be revealed once the next of kin have been informed." Follow more RNEWS articles, subscribe to our YouTube channel and for breaking news LIKE us on Facebook. For news on the Western Cape click here. For great savings on life’s little pleasures visit Bargain Buys!  Know somebody who is getting married, Wedding and Function can assist.  Have kids, then you need to visit Kids Connection. Enjoy food and travel, then visit Home Food and Travel. Need assistance with an online presence, visit Agency One. 